    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1905-02-10T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1905-02-10T00:00:00-05:00" n="289"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d289">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Cuban Minister</gloss> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Translation.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of Cuba</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1905-02-10">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 10, 1905</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 194.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Excellency</hi>: In compliance with the wishes of your
                    Department expressed in the memorandum of January 26, replying to mine of the
                    19th idem., I have the honor to inclose copies of testimony in the case of the
                    injury suffered by the Cuban citizen, Felipe Maza é Ibarra, at the hands of
                    United States soldiers.<note n="a" xml:id="d289fna">Not printed.</note>
                </p>
                <p>Relying upon the high spirit of justice of your excellency, I venture to ask that
                    as an act of grace toward the unfortunate citizen, Maza é Ibarra, an allowance
                    be made to relieve his miserable condition.</p>
                <p>I take, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Gonzales de Quesada.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
